{{Infobox Website |name = SIKART |logo = |screenshot = |caption = |url = http://www.sikart.ch |commercial = No |type = |language = German, French, Italian, English |registration = |owner = Swiss Institute for Art Research (SIAR) |author = Karl Jost (director) |launch date = February 2006 |current status = |revenue = |slogan = }}
'''SIKART''' is a [[biographical dictionary]] and a database on [[visual art]] in [[Switzerland]] and [[Liechtenstein]]. It is published online by the [[Swiss Institute for Art Research]] (SIAR). Conceptually and in content, it is an expanded and continually updated online version of the SIAR's 1998 ''Biographical Lexicon of Swiss Art'',<ref>{{cite book|title=Biografisches Lexikon der Schweizer Kunst|first=Karl|last=Jost|publisher=Verlag Neue Zürcher Zeitung|date=1998|editor=Schweizerisches Institut für Kunstwissenschaft|isbn=3-85823-673-X}}</ref> which featured 12,000 short entries and some 1,100 detailed biographical articles.<ref name=Masthead>{{cite web|title=Masthead|work=SIKART|url=http://sik-isea.ch/Datenbanken/SIKART/tabid/56/Default.aspx}}</ref>
==Scope== SIKART states that it is aimed at both specialists and members of the general public with an interest in art. It covers professional artists from Switzerland and Liechtenstein "who work or have worked in the genres of [[painting]], [[drawing]], [[engraving]], [[sculpture]], [[Video art|video]], [[Installation art|installation]], [[photography]], [[performance art|performance]] and [[web art]]", but not artists "who worked or work exclusively in the [[applied arts]] ([[graphic art]], [[design]], [[bell foundry]], [[gold work]], [[ceramic art|ceramics]], documentary photography, etc.)"<ref name=Masthead/>
The content is written in the language the artist is most associated with: French, Italian or German. The artists are rated with one to five stars according to their significance, which determines the depth of coverage. For all artists in SIKART, the database records the name (and any variants), the dates of birth and death, a brief [[Curriculum vitae|CV]], keywords and [[Index term|descriptors]], lexica entries, a bibliography and a link to the artist's website (if any). For artists rated with three to five stars, biographical articles of two to four pages in length are also provided, as are digital reproductions of their artworks.<ref name=Masthead/>
==Funding== SIKART is funded by the [[Swiss Confederation]], the [[Swiss cantons]] and private donors.<ref name=Masthead/> The website can be accessed free of charge, but at launch SIAR intended to charge for access at a later date so as to enable SIKART to operate independently of public funding.<ref>[http://www2.unil.ch/isea/3Services/sprojSIKonline_deu.htm Laufende Forschugsprojekte<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061111115822/http://www2.unil.ch/isea/3Services/sprojSIKonline_deu.htm |date=2006-11-11 }}</ref>
==References== *{{cite news|title=Schweizerisches Institut für Kunstwissenschaft geht online|date=14 February 2006|language=German|publisher=[[Swissinfo]]|url=http://www.swissinfo.org/ger/index.html?siteSect=203&sid=6467535|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130415214756/http://www.swissinfo.org/ger/index.html?siteSect=203&sid=6467535|dead-url=yes|archive-date=15 April 2013}} *{{cite news|title=Schweizer Kunstlexikon online|publisher=[[Netzwoche]]|language=German|date=20 February 2006|url=http://www.netzwoche.ch/(S(uwq2wvn04cdwvs55nviaplj2))/News/NewsDetail.aspx?id=28271&viewDate=1&Digest=0mtm1fP0aUwK288X9y+fYA}}
