{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
The '''Yesipov Chronicle''' (''Есиповская летопись'' in [[Russian language|Russian]]) is one of the [[Siberian Chronicles]], dedicated to the memory of [[Yermak Timofeyevich|Yermak]]. It was compiled in 1636 by Savva Yesipov, a [[podyachy]] of the [[Siberia]]n [[archbishop]] Nectarius.

